Package: spaghetti
Title: Bidirectional Spreadsheet-Formula to OOXML Translator
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("spaghetti", "authors", email = "maintainer@example.com",
  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Translates spreadsheet formulas between the user-facing format
    (as displayed to the end user) and the OOXML storage format (as found
    in .xlsx XML source). Handles future function prefixes (_xlfn.),
    web-service namespaces (_xlfn._xlws.), LAMBDA parameter prefixes
    (_xlpm.), spilled range operators (ANCHORARRAY), implicit intersection
    (SINGLE), and localised function name translation across 40+ locales.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Imports: utils
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
NeedsCompilation: no
